    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1965-07-14T17:17:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1965-07-14T17:17:00-05:00" n="150"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d150">
                <head>150. Telegram From the <gloss type="from">Department of State</gloss> to the
                        <gloss type="to">Embassy in Pakistan</gloss>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d150fn1">Source: National Archives and Records
                        Administration, <gloss target="#t_RG1">RG</gloss> 59, Central Files 1964–66,
                            <gloss target="#t_AID1">AID</gloss> 9 <gloss target="#t_Pak1"
                            >PAK</gloss>. Secret; Priority; <gloss target="#t_Exdis1">Exdis</gloss>.
                        Drafted by <persName corresp="#p_LLB1">Laingen</persName> and <persName
                            corresp="#p_LCC1">Laise</persName> on July 13, cleared by <persName
                            corresp="#p_TP1">Talbot</persName> and <persName corresp="#p_MTC1"
                            >Mann</persName>, and approved and initialed by <persName
                            corresp="#p_RD1">Rusk</persName>. Also sent to Rawalpindi.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1965-07-14T18:17:00-04:00">July 14, 1965, 6:17 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>64. <gloss target="#t_Embtel1">Embtel</gloss> 50.<note n="2" xml:id="d150fn2">
                        <ref target="#d147">Document 147</ref>.</note> For Ambassador. You should
                    thank <persName corresp="#p_SM1">Shoaib</persName> on behalf Secretary for
                    personal message conveyed <gloss target="#t_reftel1">reftel</gloss> and say that
                    Secretary appreciates confidence in our relations on which it rests. Secretary
                    strongly shares <persName corresp="#p_SM1">Shoaib</persName>’s desire that
                    crisis be avoided. Whole objective our actions and talks we seek with <gloss
                        target="#t_GOP1">GOP</gloss> is to avoid such crisis developing. He is
                    confident that <persName corresp="#p_SM1">Shoaib</persName> will do everything
                    he can to achieve same end. You should tell <persName corresp="#p_SM1"
                        >Shoaib</persName> however that considerations affecting our position on
                    timing Consortium afford U.S. no alternative and we hope he can get Ayub to see
                    this in proper perspective so that we can proceed to examine our problems and
                    find a better way to work together toward common goals.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_RD1">
                            <hi rend="strong">Rusk</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
